refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public mixedSimpleXMLElement::asXML stringfilename
The asXML method formats the parent object's data in XML version 1.0.

&reftitle.parameters;
filename
If specified, the function writes the data to the file rather than returning it.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Get XML


<?php
$string = <<<XML
<a>
 <b>
  <c>text</c>
  <c>stuff</c>
 </b>
 <d>
  <c>code</c>
 </d>
</a>
XML;

$xml = new SimpleXMLElement($string);

echo $xml->asXML();

?>


    &example.outputs;


<?xml version="1.0"?>
<a>
 <b>
  <c>text</c>
  <c>stuff</c>
 </b>
 <d>
  <c>code</c>
 </d>
</a>






   asXML also works on Xpath results:

    Using asXML() on SimpleXMLElement::xpath results


<?php
// Continued from example XML above.

/* Search for <a><b><c> */
$result = $xml->xpath('/a/b/c');

while(list( , $node) = each($result)) {
    echo $node->asXML();
}
?>


    &example.outputs;


<c>text</c><c>stuff</c>
